	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=83141><span id=Scholar>Ellon the Charming</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>37 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I just recently made a full set of Imbued Steelsilk.&nbsp;&nbsp;Under the new model, it looks like blood red fine plate.  The helmet has no graphic, but it makes the standard hood that all Erudites wear black.<br><br>To be quite honest, this would be impossible to make for a person who CAN use it at a price they can afford (and not be throwing their money away).<br><br>Here are the ingredients required to make these:<br>6 Terrorantula silks (makes 3 swatches),<br>1 vial of Purified Mana (takes 4 rubies and a poison vial to make, as well as 1000 mana),<br>1 Platinum Thread,<br>1 Tunic Pattern,<br>1 Imbued Amber;<br><br>Total cost of vendor bought items (at 120+ Cha for best prices):  Rubies = 132pp x 4 = 528pp, Platinum Thread = 210pp, Amber = 2.5pp, Tunic Pattern, Poison Vial = Negligible (less than 1pp each).  Grand total:  740.5pp.<br><br>That's already a cost of 740.5pp, WITHOUT throwing in the Terrorantula silks.  Considering the rarity of the Terroratula, the price of this armor is astronomical.  Luckily, this armor trivials at around 110 Tailoring, which means that if you raise Tailoring in order to make this, you'd only have to go up to the most minimal Wu's items.  An SK of about 35th level or higher would have no problem raising Tailoring that high, since Silks are rather easy to come by.<br><br>In the end, in my opinion, this item is for someone who is gonna throw it on a twink, someone who is really into tradeskills, who wants to make a set just for the sense of accomplishment, or, in the extreme, an Erudite SK in the middle of his career (this would be rare, as melees usually have little disposable money, unless they farm the hell out of something).<br><br>I myself put it on a twink, and, man, this is some rocking gear.  Not only do people go nuts about how cool I look, it's also nice knowing that you have a very unique setup, and if you're into roleplaying, like I am, you can pretend to be Cazic Thule's chosen and play off the Dark Lord bit, since, really, you're pretty unique and special for having such armor.<br><br>Ellon Silktongue, 51st Enchanter<br>Ellonn, 15th Shadow Knight</p>&nbsp;<br>D'Tox</td></tr>
